<br>
A druid friend I work with told me about it, and said that it is a hot item for smiths who don't want to work on tailoring.  It trivials in the 30s for tailoring, which is attainable in a matter of minutes with high INT.<br>
<br>
2 spiderling silks = silk thread.  1 silk thread + 1 LQ pelt = leather padding.  Each sells for 15-40pp in the bazaar.  I have never charged more than  20pp, coming away with 400pp per stack.<br>
<br>
Farm a bit in Everfrost for the silks, then get the hides.  For lower levels, best bet is to hunt in Karanas and get MQ hides, then use a skinning knife to make them LQ.  For mid-20s up, go to Marus Seru.  Rockhoppers drop LQ hides 4/5 of the time, and greyhopper hides the rest, which also brings good coin.  Move to Dawnshroud when the rockhoppers green/lb out.<br>
<br>
Great easy money maker, and I have never held the padding in my trader satchel for more then 30 minutes once I auction it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enyil>Enyil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/03 3:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8331.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How Much Plat Should I Have?</span><hr size=1> I didn't have much more than a couple thousand until I was lvl 51.. when Kunark came out I spent the first 6 weeks getting from lvl 50 to 55 (I really wanted COH) I spent my time in Karnors and Sebilis, the cheapest item that would drop there sold for 5k, and I sold some for as high as 50k... I ended up with a tremendous amount of cash.. bought COH for 20k (ouch!) and blew the rest on gnome hookers... (Actually I can't even remember what I spent it on)<br>
