Since then i've fluxuated between 1k and 100k... but I was pretty much broke til 51...  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=domandred>Domandred</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/03 10:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8331.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.users.qwest.net/~agentrev/images/made.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How Much Plat Should I Have?</span><hr size=1> You could have 0 plat and it won't matter if you don't have anything you need to purchase.  I have like maybe 3K to my name at level 63, but that 3K has lasted me about a month or so now because the only thing I buy is groceries bat wings, fuzzlecutter, stalking probes.  I fish so batwings goes towards food.<br>
<br>
On the other hand one of my friends plat expenses ranges in the 200 plat per day minimum on a long played day because if he doesn't have a KEI at all times he insists on going to one or he doesn't think he can play.<br>
<br>
So basically it comes down to what your expenses are + gear you think you need to buy = how much plat you should have.<br>
